The treaty effectively divided the world outside Europe into an exclusive duopoly between the Spanish and the Portuguese along a north-south meridian 370 leagues west of the Cape Verde islands. This division was never accepted by the rulers of England or France. The Treaty of Tordesillas was a significant event in the Age of Discovery, shaping colonial empires and influencing the future of many nations. Based on this information, which nation was not directly affected by the Treaty of Tordesillas?
A. Spain
B. England
C. Portugal
D. France
